Note:
DEPENDENCY MANAGER - Module Dependency Graph and Topological Ordering

This file handles dependency management and dependency resolution for the compiler.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process dependency resolution and dependency tracking operations
- Handle dependency validation and dependency consistency management
- Manage dependency optimization and dependency performance utilities
- Process dependency monitoring and dependency analysis operations

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Dependency management is fundamental to module compilation and project organization
- Proper dependency handling ensures correct compilation order and module resolution
- Dependency utilities support import resolution, module compilation, and build optimization

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- DependencyGraph with hash-indexed DependencyNode entries
- DependencyNode with name, dependency list, and DFS visit markers
- create_dependency_graph for initializing the graph
- add_module for registering modules
- add_dependency for recording module-to-module dependencies
- topological_sort using DFS-based algorithm
- detect_cycles for circular dependency detection
- get_build_order for retrieving compilation order

Dependencies:
- Imports memory_utils.runa for memory allocation
- Imports string_utils.runa for string operations
- Imports arena_utils.runa for arena-based allocation
- Imports collections.runa for ArrayList and HashTable
:End Note

Import "compiler/internal/memory_utils.runa" as MemoryUtils
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils
Import "compiler/internal/arena_utils.runa" as ArenaUtils
Import "compiler/internal/collections.runa" as Collections

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Dependency Manager Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant DEP_MAX_MODULES as Integer is 4096
Constant DEP_MAX_DEPS_PER_MODULE as Integer is 256

Note: DFS visit states
Constant DEP_UNVISITED as Integer is 0
Constant DEP_VISITING as Integer is 1   Note: Currently on the DFS stack (cycle detection)
Constant DEP_VISITED as Integer is 2    Note: Fully processed

Note: DependencyNode memory layout (56 bytes):
Note: offset  0: name (8 bytes) - Pointer to module name string
Note: offset  8: dependencies (8 bytes) - Pointer to ArrayList of dependency name strings
Note: offset 16: dependents (8 bytes) - Pointer to ArrayList of dependent module name strings
Note: offset 24: visit_state (8 bytes) - DFS visit state (DEP_UNVISITED/VISITING/VISITED)
Note: offset 32: is_resolved (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if all deps resolved, 0 if not
Note: offset 40: depth (8 bytes) - Topological depth (distance from leaf nodes)
Note: offset 48: source_path (8 bytes) - Pointer to source file path (if known)

Constant DEP_NODE_SIZE as Integer is 56

Note: DependencyGraph memory layout (56 bytes):
Note: offset  0: nodes (8 bytes) - Pointer to HashTable (module_name_hash -> DependencyNode pointer)
Note: offset  8: node_count (8 bytes) - Number of modules in the graph
Note: offset 16: arena (8 bytes) - Pointer to arena for graph allocations
Note: offset 24: has_cycles (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if cycles detected
Note: offset 32: sorted_order (8 bytes) - Pointer to ArrayList of sorted module names (cached)
Note: offset 40: is_sorted (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if sorted_order is valid
Note: offset 48: module_names (8 bytes) - Pointer to ArrayList of all module name strings (for iteration)

Constant DEP_GRAPH_SIZE as Integer is 56

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Dependency Graph Creation and Destruction
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "create_dependency_graph" takes arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a new empty DependencyGraph
    Note: Returns pointer to graph, or 0 on failure

    If arena is equal to 0:
        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Cannot create dependency graph: arena is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let graph be arena_allocate(arena, DEP_GRAPH_SIZE, 8)
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Failed to allocate dependency graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    memory_zero(graph, DEP_GRAPH_SIZE)

    Note: Create the nodes hash table
    Let nodes be hashtable_create(128, arena)
    If nodes is equal to 0:
        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Failed to create nodes hash table"
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_pointer(graph, 0, nodes)

    Note: Initialize node count
    memory_set_integer(graph, 8, 0)

    Note: Store arena
    memory_set_pointer(graph, 16, arena)

    Note: No cycles detected yet
    memory_set_integer(graph, 24, 0)

    Note: No sorted order yet
    memory_set_pointer(graph, 32, 0)
    memory_set_integer(graph, 40, 0)

    Note: Create module names list for iteration
    Let module_names be arraylist_create(64, 8, arena)
    If module_names is equal to 0:
        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Failed to create module names list"
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_pointer(graph, 48, module_names)

    Return graph
End Process

Process called "destroy_dependency_graph" takes graph as Integer returns Nothing:
    Note: DependencyGraph is fully arena-allocated, so cleanup is handled by arena_destroy.
    Note: This function exists for explicit resource management semantics.
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    Note: Invalidate the sorted cache
    memory_set_integer(graph, 40, 0)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Module Management
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "add_module" takes graph as Integer, module_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add a module to the dependency graph
    Note: Returns 1 on success, 0 on failure

    If graph is equal to 0:
        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Cannot add module: graph is null"
        Return 0
    End If
    If module_name is equal to 0:
        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Cannot add module: name is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check if module already exists
    Let nodes be memory_get_pointer(graph, 0)
    If nodes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let name_hash be dep_compute_name_hash(module_name)
    Let existing be hashtable_get(nodes, name_hash)
    If existing is not equal to 0:
        Note: Module already registered - no error, just return success
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Check maximum module count
    Let node_count be memory_get_integer(graph, 8)
    If node_count is greater than or equal to DEP_MAX_MODULES:
        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Maximum module count exceeded"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate a new DependencyNode
    Let arena be memory_get_pointer(graph, 16)
    Let node be arena_allocate(arena, DEP_NODE_SIZE, 8)
    If node is equal to 0:
        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Failed to allocate dependency node"
        Return 0
    End If

    memory_zero(node, DEP_NODE_SIZE)

    Note: Store module name (duplicate to own it)
    Let name_copy be string_duplicate(module_name)
    memory_set_pointer(node, 0, name_copy)

    Note: Create dependencies list
    Let deps be arraylist_create(16, 8, arena)
    If deps is equal to 0:
        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Failed to create dependencies list"
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_pointer(node, 8, deps)

    Note: Create dependents list (reverse deps)
    Let dependents be arraylist_create(16, 8, arena)
    If dependents is equal to 0:
        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Failed to create dependents list"
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_pointer(node, 16, dependents)

    Note: Initialize visit state
    memory_set_integer(node, 24, DEP_UNVISITED)

    Note: Not resolved yet
    memory_set_integer(node, 32, 0)

    Note: Depth = 0
    memory_set_integer(node, 40, 0)

    Note: No source path yet
    memory_set_pointer(node, 48, 0)

    Note: Insert into hash table
    Let put_result be hashtable_put(nodes, name_hash, node)
    If put_result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Add to module names list
    Let module_names be memory_get_pointer(graph, 48)
    If module_names is not equal to 0:
        Let name_for_list be string_duplicate(module_name)
        arraylist_add(module_names, name_for_list)
    End If

    Note: Increment node count
    memory_set_integer(graph, 8, node_count plus 1)

    Note: Invalidate cached sort
    memory_set_integer(graph, 40, 0)

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "add_dependency" takes graph as Integer, module_name as Integer, depends_on as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Record that module_name depends on depends_on
    Note: Both modules are auto-registered if not already present
    Note: Returns 1 on success, 0 on failure

    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If module_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If depends_on is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Ensure both modules exist in the graph
    Let add_result1 be add_module(graph, module_name)
    If add_result1 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let add_result2 be add_module(graph, depends_on)
    If add_result2 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get the dependent module's node
    Let nodes be memory_get_pointer(graph, 0)
    Let src_hash be dep_compute_name_hash(module_name)
    Let src_node be hashtable_get(nodes, src_hash)
    If src_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check if this dependency is already recorded
    Let deps be memory_get_pointer(src_node, 8)
    If deps is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let deps_count be arraylist_size(deps)
    Let already_added be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than deps_count:
        Let existing_dep be arraylist_get(deps, i)
        If existing_dep is not equal to 0:
            Let match be string_equals(existing_dep, depends_on)
            If match is equal to 1:
                Set already_added to 1
                Set i to deps_count  Note: Break
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    If already_added is equal to 1:
        Return 1  Note: Already recorded, success
    End If

    Note: Add the dependency
    Let dep_copy be string_duplicate(depends_on)
    Let add_dep_result be arraylist_add(deps, dep_copy)
    If add_dep_result is equal to 0:
        deallocate(dep_copy)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Also add the reverse dependency (depends_on is depended on by module_name)
    Let dep_hash be dep_compute_name_hash(depends_on)
    Let dep_node be hashtable_get(nodes, dep_hash)
    If dep_node is not equal to 0:
        Let dependents be memory_get_pointer(dep_node, 16)
        If dependents is not equal to 0:
            Let rev_copy be string_duplicate(module_name)
            arraylist_add(dependents, rev_copy)
        End If
    End If

    Note: Invalidate cached sort
    memory_set_integer(graph, 40, 0)

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "set_module_source_path" takes graph as Integer, module_name as Integer, source_path as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Associate a source file path with a module
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If module_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let nodes be memory_get_pointer(graph, 0)
    Let name_hash be dep_compute_name_hash(module_name)
    Let node be hashtable_get(nodes, name_hash)
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Free old source path if any
    Let old_path be memory_get_pointer(node, 48)
    If old_path is not equal to 0:
        deallocate(old_path)
    End If

    If source_path is not equal to 0:
        Let path_copy be string_duplicate(source_path)
        memory_set_pointer(node, 48, path_copy)
    Otherwise:
        memory_set_pointer(node, 48, 0)
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Topological Sort (DFS-based)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "topological_sort" takes graph as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Perform a DFS-based topological sort of the dependency graph
    Note: Returns pointer to ArrayList of module name strings in build order, or 0 on failure
    Note: Build order means dependencies come before dependents

    If graph is equal to 0:
        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Cannot sort: graph is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check if we have a cached result
    Let is_sorted be memory_get_integer(graph, 40)
    If is_sorted is equal to 1:
        Return memory_get_pointer(graph, 32)
    End If

    Let arena be memory_get_pointer(graph, 16)
    Let nodes be memory_get_pointer(graph, 0)
    If nodes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Reset all visit states to UNVISITED
    Let module_names be memory_get_pointer(graph, 48)
    If module_names is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let module_count be arraylist_size(module_names)
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than module_count:
        Let name be arraylist_get(module_names, i)
        If name is not equal to 0:
            Let name_hash be dep_compute_name_hash(name)
            Let node be hashtable_get(nodes, name_hash)
            If node is not equal to 0:
                memory_set_integer(node, 24, DEP_UNVISITED)
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Create result list
    Let result be arraylist_create(module_count plus 1, 8, arena)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Failed to create topological sort result list"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Reset cycle detection flag
    memory_set_integer(graph, 24, 0)

    Note: Visit each unvisited module
    Set i to 0
    While i is less than module_count:
        Let name be arraylist_get(module_names, i)
        If name is not equal to 0:
            Let name_hash be dep_compute_name_hash(name)
            Let node be hashtable_get(nodes, name_hash)
            If node is not equal to 0:
                Let visit_state be memory_get_integer(node, 24)
                If visit_state is equal to DEP_UNVISITED:
                    Let visit_result be dep_dfs_visit(graph, nodes, node, result)
                    If visit_result is equal to 0:
                        Note: Cycle detected
                        memory_set_integer(graph, 24, 1)
                        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Circular dependency detected during topological sort"
                        Return 0
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Cache the result
    memory_set_pointer(graph, 32, result)
    memory_set_integer(graph, 40, 1)

    Return result
End Process

Process called "dep_dfs_visit" takes graph as Integer, nodes as Integer, node as Integer, result as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: DFS visit for topological sort
    Note: Returns 1 on success, 0 if cycle detected

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let visit_state be memory_get_integer(node, 24)

    Note: If currently visiting this node, we have a cycle
    If visit_state is equal to DEP_VISITING:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: If already fully visited, skip
    If visit_state is equal to DEP_VISITED:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Mark as currently visiting (on the DFS stack)
    memory_set_integer(node, 24, DEP_VISITING)

    Note: Visit all dependencies first
    Let deps be memory_get_pointer(node, 8)
    If deps is not equal to 0:
        Let dep_count be arraylist_size(deps)
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than dep_count:
            Let dep_name be arraylist_get(deps, i)
            If dep_name is not equal to 0:
                Let dep_hash be dep_compute_name_hash(dep_name)
                Let dep_node be hashtable_get(nodes, dep_hash)
                If dep_node is not equal to 0:
                    Let visit_result be dep_dfs_visit(graph, nodes, dep_node, result)
                    If visit_result is equal to 0:
                        Return 0  Note: Propagate cycle detection
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Mark as fully visited
    memory_set_integer(node, 24, DEP_VISITED)

    Note: Add this module to the result (post-order = dependencies before dependents)
    Let module_name be memory_get_pointer(node, 0)
    If module_name is not equal to 0:
        Let name_copy be string_duplicate(module_name)
        arraylist_add(result, name_copy)
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Cycle Detection
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "detect_cycles" takes graph as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check whether the dependency graph contains any cycles
    Note: Returns 1 if cycles are detected, 0 if the graph is acyclic

    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Attempt a topological sort; if it fails, there is a cycle
    Let sort_result be topological_sort(graph)
    If sort_result is equal to 0:
        Note: Check if cycle was the reason for failure
        Let has_cycles be memory_get_integer(graph, 24)
        Return has_cycles
    End If

    Return 0  Note: No cycles
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Build Order
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "get_build_order" takes graph as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the compilation order for all modules (topologically sorted)
    Note: Returns pointer to ArrayList of module name strings, or 0 on failure
    Note: Dependencies come before the modules that depend on them

    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return topological_sort(graph)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Query Functions
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "get_module_dependencies" takes graph as Integer, module_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the list of direct dependencies for a module
    Note: Returns pointer to ArrayList, or 0 if module not found

    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If module_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let nodes be memory_get_pointer(graph, 0)
    If nodes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let name_hash be dep_compute_name_hash(module_name)
    Let node be hashtable_get(nodes, name_hash)
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return memory_get_pointer(node, 8)
End Process

Process called "get_module_dependents" takes graph as Integer, module_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the list of modules that depend on the given module
    Note: Returns pointer to ArrayList, or 0 if module not found

    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If module_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let nodes be memory_get_pointer(graph, 0)
    If nodes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let name_hash be dep_compute_name_hash(module_name)
    Let node be hashtable_get(nodes, name_hash)
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return memory_get_pointer(node, 16)
End Process

Process called "has_module" takes graph as Integer, module_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if a module exists in the dependency graph
    Note: Returns 1 if present, 0 if not

    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If module_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let nodes be memory_get_pointer(graph, 0)
    If nodes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let name_hash be dep_compute_name_hash(module_name)
    Let node be hashtable_get(nodes, name_hash)
    If node is not equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "get_module_count" takes graph as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return memory_get_integer(graph, 8)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Dependency Graph Printing
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dep_print_graph" takes graph as Integer returns Nothing:
    Note: Print the dependency graph for debugging
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Alert "[DEP ERROR] Cannot print graph: graph is null"
        Return
    End If

    Display "--- Dependency Graph ---"

    Let module_names be memory_get_pointer(graph, 48)
    If module_names is equal to 0:
        Display "  (empty)"
        Return
    End If

    Let nodes be memory_get_pointer(graph, 0)
    Let module_count be arraylist_size(module_names)

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than module_count:
        Let name be arraylist_get(module_names, i)
        If name is not equal to 0:
            Let name_hash be dep_compute_name_hash(name)
            Let node be hashtable_get(nodes, name_hash)
            If node is not equal to 0:
                Let deps be memory_get_pointer(node, 8)
                Let dep_count be 0
                If deps is not equal to 0:
                    Set dep_count to arraylist_size(deps)
                End If

                Let msg be string_concat("  ", name)
                Let dep_str be integer_to_string(dep_count)
                Let msg2 be string_concat(msg, " -> ")
                deallocate(msg)
                Let msg3 be string_concat(msg2, dep_str)
                deallocate(dep_str)
                deallocate(msg2)
                Let msg4 be string_concat(msg3, " dependencies")
                deallocate(msg3)
                Display msg4
                deallocate(msg4)

                Note: Print each dependency
                If deps is not equal to 0:
                    Let j be 0
                    While j is less than dep_count:
                        Let dep_name be arraylist_get(deps, j)
                        If dep_name is not equal to 0:
                            Let dep_msg be string_concat("    -> ", dep_name)
                            Display dep_msg
                            deallocate(dep_msg)
                        End If
                        Set j to j plus 1
                    End While
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Display "------------------------"
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal Helper Functions
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dep_compute_name_hash" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Compute a hash of a module name string for use as a hash table key
    Note: Uses FNV-1a algorithm

    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let hash be 2166136261
    Let len be string_length(name)
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than len:
        Let byte_val be memory_get_byte(name, i)
        Let xored be hash bitwise_xor byte_val
        Set hash to xored multiplied by 16777619
        Set hash to hash bitwise_and 4294967295
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    If hash is equal to 0:
        Set hash to 1
    End If

    Return hash
End Process
